trans-unit.source: Defines the interface for an STL/CLR [vector](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/f90060d5-097a-4e9d-9a26-a634b5b9c6c2) object.
The type of an element in the controlled sequence.
Replaces all elements in the container with the elements in the specified enumeration.
For more information, see [vector::assign (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/945e2048-6c61-4701-b13c-8241cbee3fa1).
The enumeration whose elements are to be inserted into the container.
Replaces all elements in the container with the elements between the given iterators.
For more information, see [vector::assign (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/945e2048-6c61-4701-b13c-8241cbee3fa1).
The beginning position of the range of elements to insert.
The first position beyond the end of the range of elements to insert.
Replaces all elements in the container with the specified number of elements that have given values.
For more information, see [vector::assign (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/945e2048-6c61-4701-b13c-8241cbee3fa1).
The number of elements to insert into the container.
The value of the element to insert.
Accesses an element at a specified position in the container.
For more information, see [vector::at (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/9af9f829-48b8-4906-ba4a-b43454acb2c7).
The position of the element to access.
The element of the controlled sequence at position _Pos.
Accesses the last element of the container.
For more information, see [vector::back (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/5edb3fcc-74c5-4f04-b8dd-edab49ba45a0).
The last element of the controlled sequence, which must be non-empty.
Accesses the last element of the container.
For more information, see [vector::back_item (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/9658ffa8-7bde-4242-9ed9-ca42be0d1433).
The last element of the controlled sequence, which must be non-empty.
Designates the beginning of the controlled sequence.
For more information, see [vector::begin (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/f9cdf854-0770-4334-a3dd-7f4d728a42bd).
An iterator.
Reports the size of allocated storage for the container.
For more information, see [vector::capacity (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/f82d8da9-8b4d-4288-8d18-8e9ca5911d87).
The storage that is currently allocated to hold the controlled sequence, a value at least as large as <xref href="Microsoft.VisualC.StlClr.IVector`1.size"></xref>.
Removes all elements from the container.
For more information, see [vector::clear (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/4ed20ec8-3089-4c36-b68f-1b51c639041f).
Tests whether the container has no elements.
For more information, see [vector::empty (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/c09fc4a3-bd79-4458-9a36-1d9c82ac36b1).
`true` if the container has no elements; otherwise, `false`.
Designates the end of the controlled sequence.
For more information, see [vector::end (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/21fcaf1b-7f14-4dc4-a312-fa30e631ea0d).
An iterator.
Accesses the first element of the container.
For more information, see [vector::front (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/37a36157-8220-4d5b-85b5-c6a63211a322).
The first element of the controlled sequence, which must be non-empty.
Accesses the first element of the container.
For more information, see [vector::front_item (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7db87868-3e54-4c67-a06b-01bcfff3128d).
The first element of the controlled sequence, which must be non-empty.
Accesses an element at a specified position in the container.
For more information, see [vector::operator(STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/379a7029-460d-4de8-918b-c79e3e13b9d4).
The position of the element to access.
The element at position _Pos.
Removes the last element from the container.
For more information, see [vector::pop_back (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7e9fb72c-e733-4434-a71c-e4389629a821).
Adds a new element to the end of the container.
For more information, see [vector::push_back (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/4a4c302b-e29f-4b68-b759-2f831814d896).
The value of the element to insert into the container.
Designates the beginning of the reversed controlled sequence.
For more information, see [vector::rbegin (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/fad410b9-fe79-4820-9be5-6b7e0219a1af).
An iterator.
Designates the end of the reversed controlled sequence.
For more information, see [vector::rend (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/8dc1927f-9214-468d-877e-eda20c03e90d).
An iterator.
Reserves storage to ensure the minimum growth capacity for the container.
For more information, see [vector::reserve (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/d1d5ede9-9628-4b55-95ec-f087a57205f2).
The new minimum capacity of the container.
Changes the number of elements in the container to the specified size.
For more information, see [vector::resize (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/a3556fbc-67d9-463a-9ffc-cb43ee15657f).
The new size of the controlled sequence.
Changes the number of elements in the container to the specified size.
If the new size is larger than the old size, the method appends elements that have value _Val.
For more information, see [vector::resize (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/a3556fbc-67d9-463a-9ffc-cb43ee15657f).
The new size of the controlled sequence.
The value of the elements to insert.
Counts the number of elements in the container.
For more information, see [vector::size (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/3d2a156e-5871-4441-9307-21a20cd1430f).
The length of the controlled sequence.
Swaps the contents of two containers.
For more information, see [vector::swap (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/9ad083fe-f79b-4b97-8013-581fd00c059a).
The container with which to swap contents.
